commitResults.messageTitle: Completed level 1. Greet, Echo, Exit for Duke
Completed Level 8 branch. Dates and Times

commitResults.messageBody: Following Google's Java Style Guide as much as possible.

commitResults.messageTitle: Adds basic GUI functionality to Duke.
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit adds up to Tutorial-3 in the JavaFX tutorial for
adding a GUI to Duke. To run this portion, you are required to
change your run configurations to have it run the gradle:run task
instead of the standard java program from IntelliJ.

Previously, duke was a purely CLI program which interacted
with user through text.

With the new GUI functionality, users are now able to view a GUI
for duke which will help enhance usability and experience for them.

In the future, there is a hope to spiff up the look of the duke
GUI to make it more appealing to users.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code to be more readable
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, there were multiple checkstyle violations that were
happening in the codebase. Now, the gradle task for checkstyleMain
gives no errors and the code is conforming to the coding standard
provided by CS2103T.

commitResults.messageTitle: Adds better exception handling capabilities to Duke
commitResults.messageBody:
With this commit, duke is now able to handle more types of events
that can cause the program to not function as expected. An additional
exception is if the stored data was somehow corrupted and its data
is not retrievable. Also, refactored out some code exception handling
code to better reflect locality of exception catching.

commitResults.messageTitle: Rename packages and refactor out AddCommand
commitResults.messageBody:
To comply with internet standards, renamed com.chee to duke package
as domain name is not registered. Also, refactored out AddCommand
to their specific task commands for cleaner code.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assert statements to prevent programmer mistakes. (#4)
commitResults.messageBody:
The assert statements will ensure that the program holds up at
various points of executions. Mostly ensuring that objects being
used are non-null.

commitResults.messageTitle: Enhance readability of code across codebase
commitResults.messageBody:
Refactor out apprpopriate portions of the codebase to add to the
readability of the codebase. Method extractions were heavily used
to comply with SLAP. Also, extra classes for
global variables were created to package code into one place.

Corrects checkstyle violations happening in the codebase.
This was alerted through the travis CI build automation used in
previous commits.

Duke is now able to handle tag commands and allows tagging of
tasks as user sees fit. Usage of the command is of the following
syntax: tag <task number> /as <tag>

Also, ToDoTest has been rewritten taking into account the tagging
functionality.
